# Security configuration items can be set here. This file should be kept
# encrypted at rest. Encrypt this file to secure.gpg and delete the original.
#
# When Mutt is executed, it will call gnupg to descrypt
# the file and keep settings in memory, preventing you from having to maintain
# passwords in a cleartext file.

# Account-specific IMAP usernames and passwords
#
# Set imap_user in a folder-hook for gmail accounts so it can be reused as
# the from address when composing mail. This simplifies configuration in
# muttrc, saving you from having to type your email address yet again.
folder-hook  '\@gmail.com' 'set imap_user=cal@gmail.com'
account-hook '\@gmail.com' 'set imap_pass="hackme123"'
